\sum_{k=1}^\infty \frac{a_k}{k}
\sum_{k=1}^\infty a_k
c
 a_k=\frac{(-1)^{k+1}}{\left\lfloor{\Large\frac{k+1}2}\right\rfloor} 
 \begin{align} \sum_{k=1}^\infty a_k &=\sum_{k=1}^\infty\frac1k(1-1)\\[6pt] &=0 \end{align} 
 \begin{align} \sum_{k=1}^\infty\frac{a_k}{k} &=\sum_{k=1}^\infty\frac1k\left(\frac1{2k-1}-\frac1{2k}\right)\\ &=\sum_{k=1}^\infty\left(\frac2{2k-1}-\frac2{2k}-\frac1{2k^2}\right)\\ &=2\log(2)-\frac{\pi^2}{12}\\[10pt] &\stackrel.=0.563827327695778 \end{align} 
 \left|\,\sum_{k=1}^\infty\frac{a_k}{k}\,\right|\le c\,\left|\,\sum_{k=1}^\infty a_k\,\right| 
